{"key":"post-19198211","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19198211</id>\n<content>OK, we have a problem here with terminology.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;'Frosting Layer' refers to the bad practice of leaving a layer of grains exposed on the surface.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Covering the exposed grains with a bit of coir or whatever substrate is the correct thing to do.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Coir often starts fruiting before it's fully colonized.&amp;nbsp; Many times it's from looking at it too much, lowering the CO2 level which is a pinning trigger.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19198412</next>\n<prev>19197704</prev>\n<first>19197257</first>\n<last>19198485</last>\n<when>1385609717</when>\n<utime>11/28/13 05:35 AM</utime>\n</post>"}